analysis.significance: Documents key news stories from September 24, 2018, including the potential resignation/firing of Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein and its implications for the Mueller investigation

notable_quotes: Some reports this morning alleged that the deputy attorney general had resigned. Others claimed he was on his way to the White House to be fired.
In the likely case that Rosenstein is on his way out, can the Mueller investigation survive?
Bill Cosby will be sentenced this week for sexual assault.

public_knowledge.context: This appears to be an Apple News digest summarizing publicly reported news stories from September 2018 about Rod Rosenstein's status, Bill Cosby sentencing, Tiger Woods' comeback, fall travel destinations, and TV premieres

analysis.summary: This Apple News digest from September 24, 2018 covers multiple news stories including conflicting reports about Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein's potential resignation/firing and its impact on the Mueller investigation, Bill Cosby's upcoming sentencing for sexual assault, Tiger Woods' golf comeback victory, autumn travel destinations, and fall TV premieres including Magnum P.I. and Big Bang Theory.
